  "body": "\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `Geth/v1.8.12-unstable-598f786a/linux-amd64/go1.10.3`\r\nOS & Version:Linux\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nWhen you search for a negative block number, it should return an error stating that \r\n\r\n```\r\n\"Can't search for negative block-number. Only non-negative blockNumbers expected\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nWhen `blockNumber<0`\r\n`eth.getBlock(i, true);` \r\nreturns \r\n```\r\nError: invalid argument 0: hex string without 0x prefix\r\n        at web3.js:3143:20\r\n        at web3.js:6347:15\r\n        at web3.js:5081:36\r\n        at getTransactionsByAccount (/root/files/js/getTransactionsByAccount.js:16:18)\r\n        at <anonymous>:1:43\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nIn a geth console,\r\n`eth.getBlock(-1, true);`\r\nIn place of -1 any negative number can be tried\r\n\r\n",
